    <div class="bildtext">  
        <h2><!--#echo var="title" --></h2>
        <p class="justify">Pulses of sound are "pushed" on a (convulted) conductor by magnetostrictions (fast constriction of conductor because of a strong magnetic field). This information runs with (the material's) sonic speed to the end and is reconverted in electric pulses. Now the information were lost if it would not be reconverted and feeded into the conductor again.</p>
        <p class="justify">Thus the data permanently go in circles and can be read and changed when they quit the conductor. The longer the conductor, the bigger the capacity.</p>
        <p class="justify">It is a non-permanent storage with a comparatively long access time. If you turn of the computer, all data is lost.</p>
